# Plan: Consistent Claims — Central JWT Token Factory

## Goal

Eliminate scattered `JwtTokenBuilder` call sites across controllers. Introduce a single `IMagiqJwtTokenFactory` service that owns all claim construction and JWT issuance. Align claim type names across JWT and OIDC (IS4) paths.

---

## Problems

### 1. Inline `JwtTokenBuilder` — 5 sites, inconsistent claims

| Location | Claims emitted | Missing |
|---|---|---|
| V1 `LoginCustomerInternal` | `given_name`, `family_name`, `MembershipId` | `LoginID`, `CustomerName` |
| V1 `LoginCustomersInternal` | `given_name`, `family_name`, `MembershipId` | `LoginID`, `CustomerName` |
| V2 `LoginCustomerInternal` | `given_name`, `family_name`, `MembershipId` | `LoginID`, `CustomerName` |
| V2 `LoginCustomersInternal` | `given_name`, `family_name`, `MembershipId` | `LoginID`, `CustomerName` |
| V2 `Verify` (post-2FA) | `MembershipId` only | `given_name`, `family_name` — **plus wrong issuer** |

### 2. Issuer inconsistency
- All login endpoints: `"https://" + domain` ✓
- V2 `Verify`: hardcoded `"MagiqCloud"` ✗

### 3. `JwtTokenBuilder.AddClaims` silently broken
```csharp
// JwtTokenBuilder.cs:53 — LINQ Union returns IEnumerable, never mutates this.claims
this.claims.Union(claims);  // BUG: no-op
```

### 4. `UserProfileService` hardcodes claim name strings
```csharp
new Claim("LoginID", ...)     // should use MagiqClaimsFactory.LoginId
new Claim("ClientName", ...)  // should use MagiqClaimsFactory.ClientName
new Claim("TenantId", ...)    // no constant defined yet
```

### 5. Claim type mismatch between JWT and OIDC paths
- `MagiqClaimsFactory` defines `given_name` / `family_name` (short OIDC form)
- `UserProfileService` emits `ClaimTypes.GivenName` / `ClaimTypes.Surname` (long MS URN)
- Consumers receive different claim type strings depending on which auth path was used

### 6. `CookieAuthenticationService` and `IDPAuthenticationService` have identical `SignIn` bodies

---

## Breaking Change Analysis

| Change | Risk | Verdict |
|---|---|---|
| `AddClaims` bug fix | No callers exist in codebase | ✅ Safe |
| `TenantId` constant | Additive | ✅ Safe |
| New claims in `BuildCustomerToken` (`LoginID`, `CustomerName`) | Additive — consumers ignore unknown claims | ✅ Safe |
| `JwtClaimTypes.GivenName` → `MagiqClaimsFactory.GivenName` | Same string value (`"given_name"`) — identical output | ✅ Safe |
| `UserProfileService`: `ClaimTypes.GivenName` → `MagiqClaimsFactory.GivenName` | IS4 outbound mapper converts long URN → `given_name` before emitting; output is identical. No internal code reads `ClaimTypes.GivenName` from `IssuedClaims`. | ✅ Safe |
| V2 `Verify` issuer `"MagiqCloud"` → `"https://" + domain` | `ValidIssuer = "https://" + domain` in `ServiceCollectionExtensions.cs:297` — tokens with issuer `"MagiqCloud"` already fail JWT bearer validation. Current Verify flow is non-functional. Fix corrects a live bug. | ✅ Safe (fixes broken) |

### Guard — do NOT change in Step 2

`UserProfileService.cs:42` uses `ClaimTypes.Name` for the username claim — leave it as-is. `UserStore.cs` reads `ClaimTypes.Name` from external IDP token claims in unrelated flows; changing this line would risk collateral damage.

```csharp
// Line 42 — leave ClaimTypes.Name unchanged
context.IssuedClaims.Add(new Claim(ClaimTypes.Name, user.Username));
```

